Problem
What Perclias solves
Doctors lose time manually capturing patient conversation data. Perclias acts as an AI clinical assistant — recording, transcribing, analyzing, and surfacing relevant medical knowledge so doctors can focus on diagnosis rather than note-taking.

Data layer
Medication knowledge base
BeautifulSoup + Selenium scraped MedlinePlus for drug/medication data. Pydantic validated the schema. Apache Airflow DAGs orchestrated the pipeline. Data landed in Snowflake for structured SQL queries, and embeddings went to Pinecone for semantic vector search.

AI layer
Conversation intelligence
Doctor-patient audio is captured, uploaded to AWS S3, then transcribed via OpenAI Whisper. The transcript is processed with LangChain + GPT to extract symptoms, summarize findings, and generate recommendations — grounded in the Pinecone knowledge base (RAG).

Vision layer
Medical image analysis
Google Gemini Vision Pro analyzes uploaded medical images (X-rays, scans, etc.) and returns structured clinical observations — helping doctors get AI-assisted second opinions on visual diagnostics.

Interface + auth
Doctor-facing app
Streamlit powers the UI — login, patient management, audio recording, image upload, and chat. Firebase handles authentication. The app was deployed on Google Cloud Platform (GCE VM).


